# =============================================================================
# geometry/2D_molaro_axisym_T-5pair.opts — Molaro et al. (2019) -5 C pair,
# AXISYMMETRIC. Pair with experiment/molaro_T-5_h1.00_arrh.opts.
#
# The -5 C series' OWN grains (their Table: diameters 197/153 um at t=0):
#   R = 98.5 / 76.5 um, t=0 neck WIDTH 32.51 um.
# Both differ from the -20 C pair (202/145 um, neck 32.81), hence a separate
# geometry — the two series are different grain pairs, not the same pair at
# two temperatures.
#
# eps = 3.9e-7 is shared with 2D_molaro_axisym_T-20pair.opts so the
# temperature comparison is not confounded by discretization. This file is
# the BINDING one for that choice: at the Arrhenius alpha_c = 7.29e-2 for
# -5 C, the K&P heat-channel ceiling is 3.94e-7 (comp_eps.py --T0 -5
# --alpha 7.29e-2 -> Eq.43a D*_ia binding), so eps must sit under it. Note
# this leaves only ~1% headroom: if alpha_c at -5 is revised UPWARD, eps
# must shrink and BOTH geometries must be re-calibrated.
#
# CAVEAT (inherited, see .claude/ACTIVITY_LOG.md 2026-07-14): the ceiling
# uses the D*_ia heat channel. On the conservative pure-ice channel this eps
# is ~8.6x past the ceiling and the thin-interface correction has flipped
# sign. If this run shows interface-kinetics artifacts, that is the first
# suspect — re-derive with comp_eps.py --Dchannel ice.
#
# NECK CALIBRATION — DO NOT HAND-EDIT -ice_grain_cx. The IC sums diffuse
# grain fields, so the measured phi=0.5 waist exceeds the sharp chord by
# +4.93 um here (sharp 27.58 -> measured 32.51). Re-solve on any eps change:
#
#   python preprocess/calibrate_neck_geometry.py --axisym \
#       --R0 7.65e-5 --R1 9.85e-5 --neck 32.51e-6 --eps <new_eps>
#
# Values below are its output at eps = 3.9e-7 (measured neck 32.510 um,
# error < 0.1 nm).
#
# VERIFY AT RUNTIME:
#   python postprocess/neck_width.py <run_dir> --axisym
# =============================================================================

-axisym 1

-ic_type multi_grains
-dim 2
-Lx 3.87776e-04
-Ly 1.18500e-04
-Lz 0

-ice_grain_cx 9.65000e-05,2.69276e-04   # separation d = 1.727762e-04 m
-ice_grain_cy 0.0,0.0
-ice_grain_R  7.65e-5,9.85e-5
-ice_grain_ax 7.65e-5,9.85e-5
-ice_grain_ay 7.65e-5,9.85e-5

-Nx 1407                                # h = eps/sqrt(2)
-Ny 430
-Nz 1
-eps 3.9000e-07

-delt_t 1.0e-4
-periodic 0
